snippet.title: HIM | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
What would you sacrifice to become the greatest of all time?

From Oscar® winner Jordan Peele and Monkeypaw Productions, producers of the landmark horror films Get Out, Us, Candyman and Nope, comes a chilling journey into the inner sanctum of fame, idolatry and the pursuit of excellence at any cost, featuring an electrifying dramatic performance from Marlon Wayans (Air, Respect).

Former college wide-receiver Tyriq Withers (Atlanta, the upcoming I Know What You Did Last Summer) plays Cameron Cade, a rising-star quarterback who has devoted his life, and identity, to football. On the eve of professional football’s annual scouting Combine, Cam is attacked by an unhinged fan and suffers a potentially career-ending brain trauma.

Just when all seems lost, Cam receives a lifeline when his hero, Isaiah White (Marlon Wayans), a legendary eight-time Championship quarterback and cultural megastar, offers to train Cam at Isaiah’s isolated compound that he shares with his celebrity influencer wife, Elsie White (Julia Fox; Uncut Gems, No Sudden Move). But as Cam’s training accelerates, Isaiah’s charisma begins to curdle into something darker, sending his protégé down a disorienting rabbit hole that may cost him more than he ever bargained for.

The film features a dynamic supporting cast including alternative comedy legend Tim Heidecker (First Time Female Director, Us) and Australian comic Jim Jefferies (The Jim Jefferies Show), plus MMA heavyweight fighter Maurice Greene and hip hop phenoms Guapdad 4000 and Grammy nominee Tierra Whack, all three in their feature film debuts.

HIM is directed by Justin Tipping (Kicks) from an acclaimed Black List screenplay by Zack Akers & Skip Bronkie (creators of the sci-fi crime series Limetown) and by Justin Tipping. The film is produced by Ian Cooper (Nope, Us), Jordan Peele (Candyman, BlacKkKlansman), Win Rosenfeld (Candyman, Lovecraft Country) and Jamal M. Watson (Hala, Sprinter) for Monkeypaw Productions and is executive produced by David Kern and Monkeypaw’s Kate Oh.

Follow HIM on socials: 
https://www.instagram.com/himmovie/
https://www.facebook.com/himmovie/
https://twitter.com/himmovie/
https://www.himmovie.com/

Cast:​Marlon Wayans, Tyriq Withers, Julia Fox, Tim Heidecker, Jim Jefferies 
Director:​​​Justin Tipping
Screenplay by:​Zack Akers & Skip Bronkie and Justin Tipping

snippet.title: Kambua – HAKAWII (Official Music Video) SKIZA 95211119
snippet.description:
HAKAWII 
A soul-stirring anthem of trust, patience, and God’s perfect timing.

Performed by Kambua, written, produced, and directed by J Blessing, Hakawii reminds us that God is never late. He works in silence, shapes us like a potter with clay, and always shows up right on time.

🎧 Listen/Download here: https://onerpm.link/hakawii


Credits:
✍🏽 Written, Produced & Directed by: J Blessing
🎥 Video AD: Don Ibrah
💡 Lights & Set Design: Jerry
🏃🏽 Set Runner: Sebbi Humain
📜 Script: BBB
🎭 Casting Director: Dantez
🎚 Audio Production: Saint P
🎛 Mixed & Mastered: SoFresh
👥 Cast: Jane, Saint P, Tim Chege, Kambua Kids
🎬 Kambua Assistant: Lucy Sonnie
color grading : I-Director 
backup singers: Mbire and Joan 

🎵 HAKAWII – Kambua

(Swahili lyrics with English translation)

⸻

Nimeomba… nimesubiri
[I have prayed… I have waited]
Najua… Hakawii
[Now I know… He’s never late]
Hajawahi kuchelewa
[He has never been delayed]

⸻

VERSE 1

Sauti yako haijawahi nyamaza
[Your voice has never been silent]
Nilipoona kimya, Wewe ulikuwa ukitenda
[When I thought you were silent, You were at work]
Sikuona mlango ukifunguka
[I didn’t see the door open]
Lakini ulituma neema kabla ya mlango kuonekana
[But You sent grace before the door appeared]
Nifikiri umeniacha
[I thought You had left me]
Lakini ulikuwa karibu kuliko pumzi
[But You were closer than my breath]
Wakati wangu ulikuwa mpangoni
[My time was in Your plan]
Na jina lako likawa sahihi kwa saa zote
[And Your name proved right in every moment]

⸻

PRE-CHORUS 1

We ni Mungu wa ahadi
[You are the God of promise]
Na Simdogo wa miujiza
[And not limited in miracles]
Majira yako ni ya milele
[Your seasons are eternal]
Na moyo Wako hausahau
[And Your heart never forgets]

⸻

CHORUS

Hakawii… Mungu wangu hakawii
[Never late… My God is never late]
Kila chozi lina majira
[Every tear has its timing]
Na kilio kina sauti Yake
[And every cry carries His voice]
Hakawii… Hakawii
[Never late… Never late]
Yuko sahihi – hata nisipoelewa
[He’s always on time – even when I don’t understand]

⸻

VERSE 2

Wengine walicheka nikiwa nangoja
[Some laughed while I was waiting]
Wakaniambia, “mbona hajibu kama yupo?”
[They asked, “Why doesn’t He answer if He’s real?”]
Lakini sasa naona kwa macho ya roho
[But now I see with the eyes of the spirit]
Hakuna hasara kwa anayemngojea Bwana
[There’s no loss in waiting on the Lord]
Nililia bila majibu
[I cried with no answers]
Nikafunga bila kuona ishara
[I fasted without seeing signs]
Lakini moyo wangu haukuwahi kuwa pweke
[But my heart was never alone]
Kwa sababu polepole, alinijenga kuwa shahidi
[Because slowly, He was building me up to be a witness]

⸻

PRE-CHORUS 2

Wakati Wake… ni ushuhuda wangu
[His timing… is my testimony]
Haandiki kwa haraka
[He does not write in haste]
Ahadi za nizamilele
[His promises are eternal]
Hakawii
[Never late]
Na anajua kila dakika ya machozi yangu
[And He knows every minute of my tears]

⸻

CHORUS – REPEAT

Hakawii… Mungu wangu hakawii
[Never late… My God is never late]
Kila chozi lina majira
[Every tear has its season]
Na kilio kina sauti Yake
[And every cry carries His voice]
Hakawii… Hakawii
[Never late… Never late]
Yuko sahihi – hata nisipoelewa
[He is right on time – even when I don’t understand]

Hakawii… Mungu wangu hakawii
[Never late… My God is never late]
Kila chozi lina majira
[Every tear has its timing]
Na kilio kina sauti Yake
[And every cry carries His voice]
Hakawii… Hakawii
[Never late… Never late]
Yuko sahihi – hata nisipoelewa
[He is right on time – even when I don’t understand]

snippet.title: Single Dee & Alikiba - Focus (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Music video by Single Dee & Alikiba performing “FOCUS”, is a cross-border masterpiece where the smooth, soulful touch of Tanzania’s Alikiba meets the fresh, vibrant energy of South Sudan’s Single Dee. The track blends East African rhythms with modern Afro-fusion vibes, carrying a message of determination, love, and keeping your eyes on what truly matters. Sung in a rich mix of Swahili, English, and Arabic, the song becomes a cultural bridge showcasing heritage, unity, and the beauty of African diversity. Alikiba’s silky vocals glide effortlessly over the beat, while SingleDee adds a distinctive flavor that connects different worlds and stories. Together, they create a song that feels like a warm sunrise hopeful, inspiring, and irresistibly groovy. The music video was shot in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania Directed by Creator Pro & Audio Produced by Andy Muzik.

snippet.title: Harmonize & Abigail Chams - Lala (Official Lyrics Audio)
snippet.description:
After a string of successful collaborations, Tanzanian superstars Harmonize and Abigail Chams reunite for a deeply emotional and melodically rich new single titled “Lala.” This marks their fourth joint project, following fan-favorites “Closer,” “Leave Me Alone,” and “Me Too.”

Produced by Cukie Dady, “Lala” is a soulful of Bongo Fleva and soft Afro-pop, built around a tender theme of intimacy, emotional vulnerability, and timeless love. Harmonize pours his heart out as he sings about finally falling deeply in love expressing joy he’s never felt before and a desire to spend forever with his partner. His words, “You smell like honey, you're the only one,” paint a vivid picture of romantic admiration.

Abigail Chams responds with heartfelt emotion, sharing the internal conflict of trying to resist love but ultimately surrendering to it. Her vocals are soft yet striking as she confesses, “Why ghafla nakuita honey hivi mapenzi kitu gani, I don’t know why.” There’s a sense of honesty and youthful vulnerability in her delivery, making the record even more relatable.

The chorus, “Kifuani lalaa usinzie” (Lay on my chest, Fall asleep), becomes a comforting refrain a symbolic invitation into a safe space of love, peace, and emotional connection.

With unmatched chemistry and heartfelt storytelling, Harmonize and Abigail Chams once again deliver a song that resonates deeply. “Lala” is not just a duet it's a musical embrace that reminds listeners of the beauty of finding love, and the comfort of being seen, heard, and held.

🔵 PSG vs Tottenham 2-2 (4-3 pens) | UEFA Super Cup 2025 | Highlights & All Goals

*📝 Description:*  
Paris Saint-Germain staged a remarkable comeback to clinch their first UEFA Super Cup title, defeating Tottenham Hotspur 4-3 in a penalty shootout after a 2-2 draw in regulation time. Tottenham took a commanding 2-0 lead with goals from Micky van de Ven and Cristian Romero. However, PSG responded with late goals from Lee Kang-in and Gonçalo Ramos to level the match. In the ensuing shootout, Nuno Mendes scored the decisive penalty, securing the victory for PSG. [1]
